Examining the Data

My dataset consists of annual Gila Monster home range estimates and a variety of environmental variables quantifying different aspects of precipitation, temperature, and vegetation productivity.

Effect of Vegetative Productivity on Annual Home Range Size

Now Ill create and analyze a linear model testing for the effect of vegetative productivity, measured by average annual MSAVI2, on annual WAKDE home range size

#creating a linear model of WAKDE home range size and MSAVI2
model_1 <- lm(WAKDE ~ Avg.MSAVI2, data = Env.HR)
anova(model_1)

Now Ill plot the MSAVI2 values and the home range estimates

Effect of Active Season Precipitation on Home Range Size

Now Ill create and analyze a linear model testing for the effect of active season precipitation on annual WAKDE home range size

#creating a linear model of WAKDE home range size and active season precipitation
model_2 <- lm(WAKDE ~ Avg.AS.Precip, data = Env.HR)
anova(model_2)

Next Ill create a point plot comparing average active season (March-August) precipitation and annual home range size
